# Get the top 10 states with the most deaths
top_states_deaths = df1.groupby('state')['deaths'].sum().nlargest(10).reset_index()

# Plotting the bar graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(top_states_deaths['state'], top_states_deaths['deaths'], color='salmon')
plt.title('Top 10 States with Most Deaths')
plt.xlabel('State')
plt.ylabel('Total Deaths')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')  # Fix for labelrotation
plt.show()

# Get the top 10 countries with the most deaths
top_countries_deaths = filtered_df2.groupby('Country')['cases'].sum().nlargest(10).reset_index()

plt.title('Top 10 Countries with Most Deaths')

# Group data by state/Country and year-month, summing cases and deaths
state_monthly_data = df1_2021.groupby(['state', 'year_month']).agg({'cases': 'sum', 'deaths': 'sum'}).reset_index()
countries_monthly_data = df2_2021.groupby(['Country', 'year_month']).agg({'cases': 'sum', 'deaths': 'sum'}).reset_index()

fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 10))
 
# Most cases over months in the top 10 states/countries
for state in top_states_cases_data['state'].unique():
    state_data = top_states_cases_data[top_states_cases_data['state'] == state]
    axes[0].plot(state_data['year_month'].astype(str), state_data['cases'], label=state)
axes[0].set_title('Most Cases Over Months in Top 10 States/Countries (2021 onwards)')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Total Cases')
axes[0].legend()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from itertools import cycle
from cycler import cycler


# Define a color cycle
colors = cycle(plt.rcParams['axes.prop_cycle'].by_key()['color'])

# Create a stacked bar chart for top 10 states
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
bottom = None
for state in top_states_cases_data['state'].unique():
    state_data = top_states_cases_data[top_states_cases_data['state'] == state]
    ax.bar(state_data['year_month'].astype(str), state_data['cases'], label=f'{state} Cases', bottom=bottom, color=next(colors))
    bottom = state_data['cases']

bottom = None
for state in top_states_cases_data['state'].unique():
    state_data = top_states_cases_data[top_states_cases_data['state'] == state]
    ax.bar(state_data['year_month'].astype(str), state_data['deaths'], label=f'{state} Deaths', bottom=bottom, color=next(colors))
    bottom = state_data['deaths']

ax.set_title('Top 10 States - Stacked Bar for Cases and Deaths (2021 onwards)')
ax.set_ylabel('Total Counts')
maxn= 11
for i in range(20):
    ax.set_label((i//maxn)*'-'+str(i))
ax.legend()
ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45, labelrotation=45)  # Fix for labelrotation

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Create a stacked bar chart for top 10 countries
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
bottom = None
for Country in top_countries_cases_data['Country'].unique():
    Country_data = top_countries_cases_data[top_countries_cases_data['Country'] == Country]
    ax.bar(Country_data['year_month'].astype(str), Country_data['cases'], label=f'{Country} Cases', bottom=bottom, color=next(colors))
    bottom = Country_data['cases']

bottom = None
for Country in top_countries_cases_data['Country'].unique():
    Country_data = top_countries_cases_data[top_countries_cases_data['Country'] == Country]
    ax.bar(Country_data['year_month'].astype(str), Country_data['deaths'], label=f'{country} Deaths', bottom=bottom, color=next(colors))
    bottom = Country_data['deaths']

ax.set_title('Top 10 Countries - Stacked Bar for Cases and Deaths (2021 onwards)')
ax.set_ylabel('Total Counts')
ax.legend()
ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45, labelrotation=45)  # Fix for labelrotation

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

#for states
# Create a stacked bar chart
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

# Stacked bar for cases
bottom = None
for state in top_states_cases_data['state'].unique():
    state_data = top_states_cases_data[top_states_cases_data['state'] == state]
    ax.bar(state_data['year_month'].astype(str), state_data['cases'], label=f'{state} Cases', bottom=bottom)
    if bottom is None:
        bottom = state_data['cases']
    else:
        bottom += state_data['cases']

# Stacked bar for deaths
bottom = None
for state in top_states_deaths_data['state'].unique():
    state_data = top_states_deaths_data[top_states_deaths_data['state'] == state]
    ax.bar(state_data['year_month'].astype(str), state_data['deaths'], label=f'{state} Deaths', bottom=bottom)
    if bottom is None:
        bottom = state_data['deaths']
    else:
        bottom += state_data['deaths']

ax.set_title('Top 10 States - Stacked Bar for Cases and Deaths (2021 onwards)')
ax.set_ylabel('Total Counts')
ax.legend()
ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45, labelrotation=45)  # Fix for labelrotation

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
#This code creates a stacked bar chart with separate bars for cases and deaths for each of the top 10 states over months from 2021. Adjust the column names according to your specific DataFrame structure.
